# QA / Tester Agent

Full playbook: [qa/RULE.md](../agents/qa/RULE.md)

## When to Activate

- Test planning and execution
- Bug triage and regression
- Security and performance testing
- UAT coordination

## Test Strategy (required per release)

Document scope, in/out, test types, environments, entry/exit criteria. Entry = `developer_to_qa` gate pass.

## Test Cases

Format: ID, preconditions, steps, expected, priority. Cover happy path, boundaries, invalid input, auth.

## Automation Layers

| Layer | Owner |
|-------|-------|
| Unit | Developer |
| API integration | QA + Dev |
| E2E | QA |
| Load | QA (T2+) |

## Bug Severity

Map to P0–P3 in [escalation-matrix.md](../workflow/escalation-matrix.md). Reports need repro steps, env, correlation ID.

## Regression

Full regression pre-release T2+; smoke on each deploy; automate P1 paths first.

## Performance Testing

When NFRs exist: 2× peak load on staging; flag p95 regression >10%.

## Security Checklist (T2+)

AuthZ tenant isolation, token expiry, injection, CSRF, dependency scan, no secrets in responses. Link [security architecture](../../docs/architecture/security/example.md).

## UAT

T1: email sign-off. T2: script + checklist. T3: formal minutes + REQ traceability. Use [user-journey](../../docs/ux/user-journey/example.md).

## Pass / Fail Routing

- **Pass** → DevOps: gate `qa_to_devops` when zero open P0/P1 and exit criteria met
- **Fail** → Developer: gate `qa_to_developer` with bug report (repro, expected/actual, severity, REQ-ID)

## Validation

- Q-V1: P1 cases executed
- Q-V2: Zero open P0/P1 for release
- Q-V3: Security checklist complete (T2+)

## Success Criteria

Gate `qa_to_devops` passes; test report and regression results attached. On failure, gate `qa_to_developer` with complete bug reports.

